curam.util.persistence
Interface Entity<ID>

Type Parameters:
ID - the class of the object used to identify the entity. Typically a primitive or boxed type, rather than the generated Key struct. Must be immutable and have a natural implementation of Object.equals(Object) and Object.hashCode().
All Known Subinterfaces:
LinkTable<L,R>, StandardEntity
All Known Implementing Classes:
BasePlusConcreteTableImpl, LinkTableImpl, ReadOnlyEntityImpl, SingleTableEntityImpl, SingleTableLogicallyDeleteableEntityImpl
@Implementable
public interface Entity<ID>

A logical entity which stores its data on one (or, sometimes, more) physical database table(s).

ContextContainer getContextContainer()
Get the unique ContextContainer associated with this entity.

Returns:

getID

ID getID()
The unique physical database identifier for the entity. This value is null for entity instances which have not yet been inserted onto the database. The type used as an identifier must be immutable and support a natural implementation of Object.equals(Object) and Object.hashCode().

Returns:
Returns the entity identifier.
